            <!-- Hidden Dynamics - The Real Investment Opportunities -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.05) 0%, transparent 100%);">
                <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
                    <span style="font-size: 1.25rem;">üîç</span> Hidden Dynamics
                    <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: normal; color: #6b7280; margin-left: auto;">Where the real problems live</span>
                </h3>
                <p style="color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic;">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether interventions succeed or fail. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Final-Use Blind Spot</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Invisible waste:</strong> Only 15-20% of primary energy delivers useful services ‚Äî 80%+ lost before reaching end-use</li>
                            <li><strong>Supply obsession:</strong> Policy measures capacity addition (GW), not services delivered (lumens, p-km, ton-hours)</li>
                            <li><strong>Measurement gap:</strong> No tracking of useful energy ‚Äî we measure kWh sold, not outcomes achieved</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment opportunity:</strong> Energy services framing, outcome-based metrics, exergy accounting</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Pump Subsidy Trap</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Perverse incentives:</strong> Free agricultural power ‚Üí &lt;2% of 30M pumps exceed 40% efficiency <a href="https://beeindia.gov.in" style="font-size: 0.7rem;" target="_blank">[BEE]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Political capture:</strong> Electricity subsidies are electoral currency ‚Äî 25-40% savings potential untapped</li>
                            <li><strong>Hidden costs:</strong> 33 TWh/year wasted (‚Çπ20K+ Cr); efficiency can't compete with "free"</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment opportunity:</strong> Income support decoupled from consumption, feeder-level metering, ESCO models</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Labeling Theater</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>AC testing fraud:</strong> Lab test at 35¬∞C; real summer at 45-50¬∞C ‚Üí 5-star performs worse than 1-star <a href="resources.html#ref-cse-dying-wisdom-2024" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[116]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Performance gap:</strong> ACs consume 17-28% more power than rated at real temperatures</li>
                            <li><strong>Standards lag:</strong> India tests for mild climate; ignores ISO hot climate protocol (46¬∞C outside)</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment opportunity:</strong> Real-world testing protocols, dynamic efficiency ratings, enforcement</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Cooking Energy Tragedy</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Massive waste:</strong> 700M people use chulhas at 8-10% efficiency ‚Äî 90% of fuel wasted as heat/smoke <a href="https://cwejournal.org" style="font-size: 0.7rem;" target="_blank">[CWE]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Health toll:</strong> 482,000 deaths/year from household air pollution (2017)</li>
                            <li><strong>LPG gap:</strong> PMUY distributed connections but refill rates low due to cost</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment opportunity:</strong> Improved biomass stoves, electric cooking, biogas systems</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Generation Bias</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Policy asymmetry:</strong> RE gets viability gap funding + RPOs; efficiency gets voluntary programs</li>
                            <li><strong>Lobbying imbalance:</strong> Solar/wind industry organized (SECI, MNRE); efficiency diffuse, no constituency</li>
                            <li><strong>Grid planning blind:</strong> CEA projects capacity addition; never models demand reduction scenarios</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment opportunity:</strong> Negawatt markets, efficiency certificates, demand response as capacity</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Thermal Power Lock-in</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Stranded efficiency:</strong> Coal plants at 35% efficiency (design 38%) ‚Äî 65% of fuel wasted <a href="https://energy.prayaspune.org" style="font-size: 0.7rem;" target="_blank">[Prayas]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Age penalty:</strong> Efficiency degrades 1-2% for plants &gt;25 years ‚Äî but kept running for political reasons</li>
                            <li><strong>Merit order ignored:</strong> Efficient plants underutilized while inefficient plants run for state revenue</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment opportunity:</strong> Efficiency-based dispatch, accelerated retirement, waste heat recovery</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

