                </h3>
                <p style="color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic;">These systemic issues don't appear in official statistics but determine whether interventions succeed or fail. Investment here creates leverage.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Parking Subsidy</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Hidden subsidy:</strong> Free parking worth ‚Çπ1000s Cr/year ‚Äî parking tariffs far below land values <a href="https://cdn.cseindia.org" style="font-size: 0.7rem;" target="_blank">[CSE]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Land allocation:</strong> >40% of road network under on-street parking in many cities <a href="https://cdn.cseindia.org" style="font-size: 0.7rem;" target="_blank">[CSE]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Code-driven sprawl:</strong> Mandatory minimums in building codes drive car ownership</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment opportunity:</strong> Parking pricing, revenue to local services, remove minimums</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
