            <!-- Hidden Dynamics - The Real Investment Opportunities -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.05) 0%, transparent 100%);">
                <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
                    <span style="font-size: 1.25rem;">üîç</span> Hidden Dynamics
                    <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: normal; color: #6b7280; margin-left: auto;">Why reuse policies fail</span>
                </h3>
                <p style="color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic;">India mandated 20% wastewater reuse in 2008. Eighteen years later, actual reuse is 5-10%. These systemic issues explain the gap.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4>1. Policy Fragmentation <a href="resources.html#ref-teri-waste-composition-2025" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[136]</a></h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Too many agencies:</strong> MoHUA, CPCB, SPCBs, ULBs, NMCG ‚Äî no single coordinating authority</li>
                            <li><strong>Advisory, not mandatory:</strong> Most reuse policies remain guidance documents, not enforceable law</li>
                            <li><strong>No standards:</strong> No unified quality benchmarks for agricultural, industrial, or urban reuse</li>
                            <li><strong>Partner opportunity:</strong> State-level wastewater reuse cells; unified standards framework</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. The Free Water Trap</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm">
                            <li><strong>Zero price signal:</strong> Free electricity for pumps = zero incentive to conserve or reuse <a href="resources.html#ref-worldbank-water-security-2022" style="font-size: 0.7rem;">[105]</a></li>
                            <li><strong>Electoral currency:</strong> Free water/power politically untouchable ‚Äî "reform = political suicide"</li>
